  "messages": [
    {
      "id": "2e3f8d0a0e8bac78d59d3633fd24b9a6137ea0f8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 08:40:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(5 inline comments)\n\nstriping information is created during declaration only, at this time the device above doesn't usually grab any local locks. so i think it should be fine to re-use existing dt_write_lock().\n\nI tend to think if we used detached array during initialization and then setting it to ldo_stripe, we'll be fine.\n\nalso, lod_declare_attr_set() and lod_attr_set() can be optimized to ignore any changes except for uid/gid/size. with this change i was able to run your test for hours successfully (w/o that, few minutes then hit).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a9a6c16658f318309d407482c8c7f6b0ed563198",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-15 00:00:46.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 2.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "718fa523b82debf9b0d65c610ea1c54bafb0d826",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-15 00:06:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> also, lod_declare_attr_set() and lod_attr_set() can be optimized to ignore any changes except for uid/gid/size. with this change i was able to run your test for hours successfully (w/o that, few minutes then hit).\n\nI didn't do the uid/gid/size optimization. I can add it if you like---but I'm still making sure I understand the things that I think I understand.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
